            "headline": "DeFi TVL drops 27% to $156B in Q1, AI, social apps grow. Largest TVL blockchain ETH falls 37%, AI user wallets hit 2.6M. NFT volume down 25% to $1.5B.",
            "id": "67db72b2-8bf8-4b8e-b3b1-be35164bc9de",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Cointelegraph",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "The total value locked in DeFi protocols dropped to $156 billion in Q1 of 2025 due to economic uncertainty and a major exchange hack. The TVL for Ethereum fell 37% to $96 billion, while Sui saw a 44% drop to $2 billion. Solana, Tron, and Arbitrum also experienced over 30% decreases in TVL. However, Berachain was the only top-10 blockchain to increase, reaching $5.17 billion in TVL. On the other hand, AI and social apps saw growth with a 29% increase in daily unique active wallet interactions. NFT and GameFi protocols regressed in Q1, with NFT trading volume falling by 25% to $1.5 billion. Notably, OKX's NFT marketplace led in sales with $606 million, while Pudgy Penguins NFTs were the top-selling collectibles at $177 million. CryptoPunks remained popular with $63.6 million earned from 477 sales.",
